Burglars in the northern KwaZulu-Natal town of Empangeni have got all the moves.The local newspaper the Zululand Observer published a video on Thursday of three balaclava-clad intruders crawling underneath security beams of a home before gaining access through the roof and ransacking the home. Fortunately the newspaper reported no one was home at the time of the burglary. According to Crime Stats SA s website over 3 000 residential burglaries were reported to Empangeni police last year an area which is has consistently made the top 10 worst crime areas in KZN list for a number of years. Watch these burglars get low-down and dirty: 